1.Reserved keyword
2.This reserved keyword can be put at methods
3.Every object in java has an intrinsic lock or monitor lock.
4.If we call synchronized method of an object reference.We aquire intrinsic lock or monitor lock
5.For each object only one thread can aquire intrinsic lock at one time.
6.If second thread tries to aquire same intrinsic lock,it has to wait.
7.synchronized keyword is placed at methods or blocks of code.with the purpose to help in intrinstic lock aquirence when multiple thread are trying to access shared resources